            <div class=3D"pt-3 mb-0 font-size-16 pt-xl-5 mt-1 mt-xl-2">
              <p>What do particle physicists and marketers have in common?<=
/p>
<p><i>(Don=E2=80=99t worry, this isn=E2=80=99t the setup to a corny joke.)<=
/i></p>
<p><strong>Both spend a lot of time figuring out whether or not their test =
results are statistically significant.</strong></p>
<p>If you=E2=80=99ve spent any amount of time researching conversion rate o=
ptimization (CRO) and A/B testing, then you=E2=80=99ve probably come across=
 the term =E2=80=9Cstatistical significance.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p>The long and short of it is that you want to make sure your testing effo=
rts are working, and that you=E2=80=99re making data-driven decisions based=
 on your tests. That=E2=80=99s where statistical significance comes into pl=
ay.</p>
